    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>SLOWING E-ZPASS USERS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Karen DeMasters</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>E-ZPass users will risk losing passes if they thwart 5-mile-an-hour speed limit at New Jersey toll booths (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>E-ZPass was designed to speed traffic flow but if drivers use it too speedily, they risk losing their passes. Starting in January, drivers who move through the E-ZPass lanes at more than the posted 5 miles per hour will have their E-Z Pass privileges temporarily suspended. If more infractions follow, drivers could lose the pass permanently.  State troopers will be stationed at some  toll plazas.</p>
        <p>Karen DeMasters</p>
      </block>
